OL,5,CBIKE-RAGE                   Q"d8!! "d8!
OL,6,                             R/,,////,,/
OL,7, Dave Rogers from The Royal Society for 
OL,8, the Prevention of Accidents issued the 
OL,9, warning of bike-rage after a cyclist   
OL,10, had been fined forC"riding furiously"  
OL,11, in a way that would injure pedestrians.
OL,13,CAnthony Adams, 24GofCCambridge,Gwas    
OL,14, fined #120 for careless riding and for 
OL,15, not stopping when ordered by police.   
OL,17, Dave says: "Cyclists, like motorists,  
OL,18, haveCa duty to ride within the lawGand 
OL,19, to apply common sense."                
