OL,5,CBIKE-RAGE                   Q"d8!! "d8!
OL,6,                             R/,,////,,/
OL,7, The Government aims toCdouble the      
OL,8,Cnumber of cyclistsGon our roads by the 
OL,9, year 2002.                             
OL,11, A spokesman from the Department of     
OL,12, TransportGsays: "In order to do this,  
OL,13, we are addressing areas of safety,     
OL,14, security and facilities which cyclists 
OL,15, will need.                             
OL,17, "Bike-rage and road-rage come down to  
OL,18,Cpersonal responsibilityGand obeying the
OL,19, rules of the road," he adds.           
